Ekurhuleni Mayor Mzandile Masina was finally handed the keys to the slain leader's house on Thursday. JOHANNESBURG - The City of Ekurhuleni says it will be turning the home of the late South African Communist Party (SACP) leader Chris Hani into a museum and heritage site. City Mayor Mzwandile Masina was finally handed the keys to the slain leader's house on Thursday, after government spent years trying to buy it.Ekurhuleni Municipality purchases the late #SACP general secretary, #ChrisHani house to be turned into a museum to preserve struggle history pic.twitter.com/OUaqXPLUBVThe mayor's spokesperson Zweli Dlamini says: The vision of the city is to build a museum around the area. We re also looking at building a library that will have a narration centre, where people can learn about the life and times of Chris Hani. (Edited by Zamangwane Shange)